page.title: 18ECOLOGY
page.content: The damp climate produces a lush grass cover everywhere. There are many hawthorn hedgerows. We found mainly ash,elm and sycamore trees in our area although we found an odd oak,beech and silver birch. Hazel,elder and rowanberry bushes were quite common too. Although we found many different wild flowers daisies and dandelions were everywhere. Blackbirds,thrushes,magpies,rooks,star lings and sparrows are the most common birds. Other wildlife being rabbits,foxes and mice. We found ladybirds,moths,butterflies, beetles,snails and ants. There are many paths to enable people to walk through the countryside.
